abstract: Democratic 2016 presidential candidates Bernie Sanders and Hillary Rodham Clinton mount aggressive campaigns in final week before Iowa caucuses in attempts to capture female vote; both candidates use tactics undermining policies and reforms espoused by the other.
lead_paragraph: As hundreds of volunteers fanned out across the state to knock on doors, the Democratic candidates campaigned in vote-rich counties in eastern Iowa.

byline.original: By PATRICK HEALY and YAMICHE ALCINDOR
byline.contributor: Patrick Healy reported from North Liberty and Marion, Iowa, and Yamiche Alcindor from Grinnell, Iowa. John Corrales contributed reporting from Grinnell, and Nick Corasaniti from Des Moines.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton and Bernie Sanders Clash on Issues and Vie for Votes of Iowa Women
headline.print_headline: Clinton and Sanders, in Iowa, Clash on Issues and Vie for Votes of Women
